  "instructions": [
    "1. In a shallow dish, whisk together eggs, milk, and melted butter.",
    "2. Heat a non-stick skillet or griddle over medium heat.",
    "3. Dip each bread slice into the egg mixture, coating both sides evenly.",
    "4. Cook the bread slices for 2-3 minutes on each side, or until golden brown.",
    "5. Transfer the French toast to a serving plate.",
    "6. Top each slice with a spoonful of Eton mess and a few fresh berries.",
    "7. Sprinkle with granulated sugar to taste.",
    "8. Serve immediately and enjoy!"
